<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-12-06T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-12-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.01/410: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Heizer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-06T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 6,
                                        1924—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Palestine Mandate Treaty was signed at London December 3d.<note n="23" xml:id="d167fn23"><hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_212">p. 212</ref>.</note> As treaty does not enter into effect until
                            exchange of ratifications you <pb facs="0296" n="202" xml:id="pg_202"/>
                            should maintain, pending such exchange, the same position as heretofore
                            with respect to rights and duties of Consulate. Embassy London is being
                            instructed to forward copy of treaty direct to you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>